<HEAD>VP Debate, Playoff Starting Times Adjusted to Avoid Conflict</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Oct. 5 starting times for the
vice-presidential debate and the major league baseball playoffs
have been juggled to avoid a conflict, officials involved said.
   The 90-minute debate between Democrat Lloyd Bentsen and
Republican Dan Quayle was moved from a 9 p.m. EDT starting time to
8:30 p.m., officials said Tuesday.
   The start of the first game of the American League playoffs,
scheduled for the home of the East Division winner, was moved from
8:28 p.m. to 1:20 p.m., and the first pitch of game two in the
National League playoffs at Los Angeles was pushed back from 3:07
p.m. to 10:08 p.m.
   ABC will televise the baseball games. All the major networks
will televise the debate.
</TEXT>
